text: For me, I am tired of every single leading role that is given to a black actor being one where we plays a civil rights activist in a period film. The Black Panther is the only film that breaks this cycle this year. I love history and I love learning about great people but I honestly compare everything to 'the Social Network'. The fact that we know how Facebook was made but we're still watching how black people got through one moment in history. I remember learning about these key figures and they're literally picking one by one a black activist from the 30s-60s. You could find these names one after the other in the glossary of one history textbook. All of this while there are so many crazy concepts that are spinning all over the place in Hollywood set all across time. I'll definitely watch it but like.............................................................................
